---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    I’m Arthur Revelski, a Front End Software Engineer based in Boulder, Colorado. My work focuses on enhancing application efficiency, reducing costs, and ensuring accessibility compliance. I bring a blend of technical skills and practical experience to each project, aiming to drive both user satisfaction and operational excellence.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
        title="Software Engineer at ManagedMethods"
        subtitle="From July 2021 to Present, Boulder, Colorado"
    >
      <li>
        Led the development of a new product UI from the ground up, collaborating closely with backend services to design APIs, align on data models, and deliver core functionality across the stack.
      </li>
      <li>
        Led the migration of a legacy JSP and jQuery-based UI to a modern TypeScript and React architecture using Vite, significantly improving maintainability, developer velocity, and overall application quality.
      </li>
      <li>
        Improved application performance by optimizing frontend asset loading, implementing code splitting, and addressing performance bottlenecks in Spring Boot APIs through query tuning and endpoint-level optimizations.
      </li>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
        title="Software Engineer at Douglas County Schools IT Department"
        subtitle="From December 2016 to July 2021, Castle Rock, Colorado"
    >
      <li>
        Built, maintained, and enhanced production applications, diagnosing issues, implementing fixes, and ensuring stable releases across multiple district-supported platforms.
      </li>
      <li>
        Audited and remediated applications to meet WCAG accessibility standards, addressing compliance requirements and reducing legal risk across district-wide platforms.
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented unit, integration, and end-to-end testing using Jest, React Testing Library, and Cypress, increasing test coverage and providing teams with confidence when delivering changes across multiple applications.
      </li>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
        title="UX Developer at Blackboard"
        subtitle="From October 2011 to November 2016, St. Louis, Missouri"
    >
      <li>
        Designed and delivered a comprehensive design system, accelerating feature development and improving consistency across the UI/UX workflow.
      </li>
      <li>
        Acted as a bridge between UX and engineering teams, ensuring designs were technically feasible and aligned with existing design system components, helping accelerate feature delivery.
      </li>
      <li>
        Collected user feedback and conducted usability testing, incorporating insights into design and development decisions to improve product quality and user satisfaction.
      </li>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
        title="Front End Developer at SchoolCenter"
        subtitle="From March 2008 to October 2011, St. Louis, Missouri"
    >
      <li>
        Built and maintained client-facing websites within a CMS-driven environment, supporting frequent content updates and customization needs.
      </li>
      <li>
        Migrated Adobe Flash–based websites to responsive HTML solutions, ensuring cross-browser support and compatibility with early mobile devices, including iPhone.
      </li>
      <li>
        Worked closely with designers and stakeholders to translate visual designs into functional, responsive web experiences.
      </li>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>


  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5 text-justify">
    Although its hard to list everything, here's a sneak peek at tools I've worked with over the years:
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6 mb-10">
    <li>TypeScript</li>
    <li>React</li>
    <li>Vue</li>
    <li>Angular</li>
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Spring Boot</li>
    <li>React Query</li>
    <li>Zustand</li>
    <li>Redux</li>
    <li>MSW</li>
    <li>Storybook</li>
    <li>Vite</li>
    <li>Webpack</li>
    <li>Jest</li>
    <li>React Testing Library</li>
    <li>Cypress</li>
    <li>Docker</li>
    <li>CI/CD</li>
    <li>Keycloak</li>
    <li>Github Actions</li>
    <li>Google Cloud</li>
    <li>Postgres</li>
    <li>MySQL</li>
    <li>Figma</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4">
    <TimeLineElement
        title="Bachelor in Fine Arts, Communication Design"
        subtitle="2004 to 2008 at Southern Illinois University, Carbondale, Illinois"
    />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>